Key Match Events: Game 2 of the NLDS between the Dodgers and Padres was delayed after fans threw objects onto the field
Jurickson Profar robbed Mookie Betts of a home run by reaching into the stands to make the catch in left field
Post-Match Reflections: The Padres evened up the series at 1-1 with a 10-2 win over the Dodgers
Miscellaneous Highlights: Fans threw baseballs and trash onto the field, infuriating Padres outfielders Jurickson Profar and Fernando Tatis Jr.
The delay in the action lasted roughly 12 minutes
Others: Stadium security attempted to identify who the troublemakers were
Profar and Tatis both spent moments of the game interacting with the fans
